---
/**
 * context-engineering 0004 · Figure 1 — the hero "human analogy" diagram.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0004-memory-compression-and-failure-modes.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, …). In an .astro file the SVG is plain HTML, so it
 * renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers ONCE in a shared <defs> block at
 * the top of the document <body> (ids: arw, arwG, arwR, arwM). The MDX has no
 * such shared block, so the markers this figure references (arwM, arw) are
 * inlined into its own <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 286"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Human analogy: memory is your recollection of a friend, the knowledge base is the library, retrieval is looking something up, context is what's in your head while you answer."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#b5179e"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <!-- memory -->
        <rect
            x="28"
            y="30"
            width="172"
            height="88"
            rx="10"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
        <text x="114" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Memory</text
        >
        <text x="114" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >what I recall about a friend</text
        >
        <text x="114" y="88" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >our history · their prefs</text
        >
        <text x="114" y="106" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#b5179e"
            >system writes it over time</text
        >
        <!-- knowledge base -->
        <rect
            x="440"
            y="30"
            width="172"
            height="88"
            rx="10"
            fill="#eef2f7"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
        <text x="526" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Knowledge base</text
        >
        <text x="526" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >the library · encyclopedia</text
        >
        <text x="526" y="88" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >authored externally</text
        >
        <text x="526" y="106" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >read-only reference truth</text
        >

        <!-- retrieval funnel -->
        <line x1="114" y1="118" x2="276" y2="166" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <line x1="526" y1="118" x2="364" y2="166" stroke="#1f3a5a" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect
            x="232"
            y="146"
            width="176"
            height="40"
            rx="9"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="164" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Retrieval</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="178" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >the act of looking it up</text
        >

        <!-- context -->
        <line x1="320" y1="186" x2="320" y2="216" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect
            x="200"
            y="218"
            width="240"
            height="50"
            rx="10"
            fill="#efe7f0"
            stroke="#111110"
            stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="238" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Context</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="255" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >what's in my head right now, while I answer</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        One human picture for the whole lesson. <b>Memory</b> = what you remember about a friend; <b
            >knowledge base</b
        > = the library; <b>retrieval</b> = looking something up; <b>context</b> = what's in your head
        as you answer. Both stores reach the model only by being retrieved into context.<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
